Three women working within NASA&#8217;s employ defied gender and racial expectations, becoming crucial to the mission to safely send a US astronaut on a complete circuit of the Earth.With a huge amount of awards season buzz about it, catch up on the basics behind &#8220;Hidden Figures.&#8221;&#8211; What&#8217;s it about? &#8211;Katherine Johnson was one of the first African-American women hired by NASA and she made sure that she&#8217;d leave a lasting impression on the space agency.Together with fellow mathematicians Dorothy and Mary &#8212; responsible for calculating flight trajectories &#8212; they made themselves indispensable to the 1962 effort of putting an astronaut above the Earth and making sure he safely encircled it.Just as no American astronaut had orbited the Earth before, neither had anyone done what Johnson and her colleagues were attempting. That, Johnson said, shouldn&#8217;t stop it from happening now.&#8211; Who&#8217;s in it? &#8211;Heading up the impressive cast is Taraji P. Henson as Johnson herself, having been Oscar-nominated for &#8220;The Curious Case of Benjamin Button&#8221; and then winning a Golden Globe for her performance in anchoring Fox music industry drama &#8220;Empire.&#8221;Then there&#8217;s Octavia Spencer (a Golden Globe and Oscar for &#8220;The Help,&#8221; but don&#8217;t forget &#8220;Zootopia,&#8221; &#8220;Snowpiercer&#8221; and the &#8220;Divergent&#8221; movies) and Janelle Mon e has been hailed for both this and the incredible &#8220;Moonlight.&#8221;They play Dorothy Vaughan and Mary Jackson respectively.Elsewhere we have double Oscar-winner Kevin Costner leading the spaceflight taskforce, with further support from double Golden Globe-nominated Kirsten Dunst, four-time Emmy winner Jim Parsons, and another &#8220;Moonlight&#8221; alum in Mahershala Ali. Strong cast.&#8211; Who&#8217;s behind it? &#8211;Theodore Melfi only made his directorial debut in 2014, but what a way to do it, with Bill Murray feature &#8220;St. Vincent.&#8221;Allison Schroeder (of AwesomenessTV&#8217;s &#8220;Side Effects&#8221;) co-wrote with Melfi, adapting from the book by Margot Lee Shetterly.&#8211; Is it any good? &#8211;&#8220;Hidden Figures&#8221; has been nominated for a host of awards, including two at the Golden Globes, two Screen Actors Guild Awards, three Critics Choice Awards, six Black Reel Awards, and seven Satellite Awards (where it won one of several Best Cast accolades.)It was also named one of 2016&#8217;s Top 10 Films by the National Board of Review.Speaking of reviews, aggregation site Rotten Tomatoes draws a 96% approval rating from a review average of 7.7/10, while an early mid-December score of 66 could be found on Metacritic.&#8211; When&#8217;s it out? &#8211;Arriving as it does during the turn-of-the-year festive season, &#8220;Hidden Figures&#8221; gets a December 25 limited release in select US cinemas before a general bow in the US and Canada from January 6.International rollout commences not long after. Brazil commences January 19, the Philippines on January 25, the Netherlands the next day, Germany, Hong Kong and Singapore on February 2, the UK on February 17, and France from March 8, among others.&#8211; Trailers &amp; Social &#8211;Official trailer: youtu.be/5wfrDhgUMGI, facebook.com/HiddenFigures/videos/509100479296254 Facebook page: facebook.com/HiddenFigures Instagram account: instagram.com/hiddenfiguresmovie Twitter feed: twitter.com/HiddenFigures Official website: hiddenfiguresmovie.com-Relaxnews